8. To find files modified in the last 20 days AND remove files older than 20 days,

#!/bin/bash

TARGET_DIR="/path/to/your/files"

echo "Files to keep (last 20 days):"
find "$TARGET_DIR" -type f -mtime -20

echo "Deleting files older than 20 days..."
find "$TARGET_DIR" -type f -mtime +20 -exec rm {} \;

echo "Cleanup complete."


-mtime -20: Files modified within the last 20 days (i.e., you want to keep these).
-type f: Only files (not directories).
-exec rm {} \;: Deletes each matched file.

