9) shell script that searches for the word "error" in a file and removes only the word "error"


#!/bin/bash

# Set the file name
filename="yourfile.txt"

# Create a backup
cp "$filename" "${filename}.bak"

# Remove the word 'error' from all lines where it appears
sed -i 's/error//g' "$filename"

echo "'error' word removed from $filename"

